snippet.textDisplay: Obviously none of us are there and none of us know the exact circumstances, but personally I feel that they should have gotten both of them fixed before resorting to rehoming shadow. Intact male dogs will fight even if they aren’t litter mates. I’m not saying getting them fixed would have solved the problem but it’s worth a shot. This happens in most animals, one has to be the dominant one and when you add tons of testosterone pumping through them at all times it amps up the situation 10 fold.

snippet.textDisplay: I’m literally balling right now.. we hat a pretty similar situation with our dog Luna.. she was very jealous of my little sister and started to bite her (she still has scars on her arms).. so of course we decided to give her to friends because it got out of control.. she was a very lovely dog, so cute so sweet and very smart.. I really miss her even though we gave her away 4 years ago. It hurts so much when I have to witness that people have to get rid of their pets, because of complications due to behavior.. it’s not easy to “raise” a dog because it’s like a child, it needs love and affection but still rules.. you can never know how a dog reacts to other dogs (or in our case a new family member)! I feel so sorry for you guys, nobody should feel this pain.. but you can’t let them, the other dogs and you suffer from their fights somebody will get hurt.. stay strong it’s going to be a tough time❤️
